 discrimination</a> in the workplace</li>\n  <li>make <a href=\"/reasonable-adjustments-for-disabled-workers\" title=\"Reasonable adjustments for disabled workers\">reasonable adjustments</a> to your business premises if your employee is disabled</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/contract-types-and-employer-responsibilities/fixedterm-contracts","slug":"fixedterm-contracts","order":3,"title":"Fixed-term contracts","body":"<p>Fixed-term contracts:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>last for a certain length of time</li>\n  <li>are set in advance</li>\n  <li>end when a specific task is completed</li>\n  <li>end when a specific event takes place</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Fixed-term employees must receive the same treatment as full-time permanent staff.</p>\n\n<p>Find out more about <a href=\"/fixed-term-contracts\" title=\"Fixed-term employment contracts\">fixed-term employees&rsquo; rights</a>, and what to do about renewing or ending a fixed-term contract.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/contract-types-and-employer-responsibilities/agency-staff","slug":"agency-staff","order":4,"title":"Agency staff","body":"<p>As an employer, you can hire temporary staff through <a href=\"/using-a-recruitment-agency-to-find-staff\" title=\"Using a recruitment agency to find staff\">agencies</a>. This means:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you pay the agency, including the employee&rsquo;s National Insurance contributions (<abbr title=\"National Insurance contributions\">NICs</abbr>) and Statutory Sick Pay (<abbr title=\"Statutory Sick Pay\">SSP</abbr>)</li>\n  <li>it&rsquo;s the agency’s responsibility to make sure workers get their rights under working time regulations </li>\n  <li>you must make sure they can access your facilities (such as canteen and childcare facilities), and information on your job vacancies</li>\n  <li>after 12 weeks continuous employment in the same role, agency workers get the same terms and conditions as permanent employees, including pay, working time, rest periods, night w