nce contributions\">NICs</abbr> and <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax.</p>\n\n<h2>Independent contractors: working out employment status</h2>\n<p>If most of the statements below apply to someone, it&rsquo;s likely that they&rsquo;re self-employed because they:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>put in bids or give quotes to get work</li>\n  <li>have specific pieces of work or projects to do but decide how to do the work</li>\n  <li>aren&rsquo;t under direct supervision when working</li>\n  <li>can hire someone else to do the work</li>\n  <li>submit invoices for the work they&rsquo;ve done</li>\n  <li>are responsible for paying their own <abbr title=\"National Insurance contributions\">NICs</abbr> and tax</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t get holiday or sick pay when they aren&rsquo;t working</li>\n  <li>have to do unsatisfactory work again in their own time and at their own expense </li>\n  <li>are responsible for losses and taking profits from their work</li>\n  <li>can provide services to a number of different clients or customers</li>\n  <li>operate under a contract (sometimes known as a &lsquo;contract for services&rsquo; or &lsquo;consultancy agreement&rsquo;) that uses terms like &lsquo;self-employed&rsquo;, &lsquo;consultant&rsquo;, or an &lsquo;independent contractor&rsquo; </li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/employment-status/director","slug":"director","order":6,"title":"Director","body":"<p>Company directors run <a href=\"/running-a-limited-company\" title=\"Running a limited company\">limited companies</a> on behalf of shareholders.</p>\n\n<p>Directors have different rights and responsibilities from employees, and are classed as <a href=\"/employment-status/office-holder\" title=\"Office holder\">office holders</a> for tax and <a href=\"/national-insurance-contributions-for-employers\" title=\"National Insurance contributions for employers\">National Insurance contribution</a> purposes.</p>\n\n<p>If a person does other work that’s not related to being 