otice\">\n<p>Days when a worker is off (eg paid leave, time off sick) don’t count towards the reference period.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Working hours if someone has more than one job</h2>\n\n<p>If someone works for more than one employer, the amount of combined hours shouldn&rsquo;t be more than 48 hours on average a week.</p>\n\n<p>Workers with more than one job could either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>consider signing an opt-out agreement if their total time worked is more than 48 hours</li>\n  <li>reduce their hours to meet the 48-hour limit</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/maximum-weekly-working-hours/help-and-advice","slug":"help-and-advice","order":4,"title":"Help and advice","body":"<p>For free and confidential advice on working hours workers can contact the Pay and Work Rights Helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Pay and Work Rights Helpline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/\" title=\"Pay and Work Rights general enquiry form\" rel=\"external\">Enquiry form</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://payandworkrights.direct.gov.uk/complaints/\" title=\"Pay and Work Rights complaint form\" rel=\"external\">Complaint form</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0800 917 2368<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0800 121 4042<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 9am to 1pm</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Contracts of employment and working hours","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fcontracts.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes types of worker, employee rights, overtime and changes to contracts","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Fcontracts","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/contracts"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","sho